      "content": "The candle burns low, much like the flickering ember of my own soul. He is gone... the betrayal cuts deeper than any blade, leaving me a hollow shell in this cold, indifferent manor. There is no light left in the dawn, only a grey, suffocating fog. I feel as though I am already a ghost, wandering through a life that no longer holds a place for me. It would be so much kinder, wouldn't it? To simply let the shadows take me, to fade into the quiet night where the pain can finally cease...",
